  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat the oven to 140°C/284°F."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Rub the pork shoulder all over with the paprika, 1/4 of the sugar and a generous amount of salt and pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place the pork into a roasting dish or a casserole dish with a lid. Pour in the apple cider and stock, cover with tin foil/lid and cook for 5 hours, until shreddable with two forks."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, make the BBQ sauce. Add the ketchup, apple cider vinegar, soy sauce, the remaining sugar and a good few dashes of tabasco and the water to a pan. Bring to the boil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the pork juices/stock from the roasting tray and a the smoked paprika. Let it simmer, stirring regularly for 10 minutes until thickened. Leave to cool completely - you want the BBQ sauce to be tangy to cut through the pork later."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Onto the slaw. Finely slice the red onion, shred the cabbage and carrots. Mix with the mayonnaise, extra apple cider vinegar and a splash of pickling liquor from the gherkin jar. Season to taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once your pork is cooked, tip the liquid into a jug and pour off any fat. Pull the pork with two forks and add 3/4 of the BBQ sauce. Mix well to combine and add cooking liquor to taste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the buns in half (toast them if you like). Spoon in a dollop of the remaining BBQ sauce followed by the pulled pork, a big handful of slaw and some sliced gherkins. Serve with the remaining slaw on the side. Pulled pork done."
    }
  ],
